Hey, I’m Tyler

I’m a biostatistician working in clinical research. My current role is in bioinformatics, but my work ranges from building statistical models to developing software for report automation.

On this site, you can find my notes containing random experiments and code snippets I use for testing ideas, talks and papers from my past research, or learn more about me
